.TH "of_property_read_string" 9 "of_property_read_string" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
of_property_read_string \- Find and read a string from a property
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" of_property_read_string
.BI "(const struct device_node *np "  ","
.BI "const char *propname "  ","
.BI "const char **out_string "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "np" 12
device node from which the property value is to be read.
.IP "propname" 12
name of the property to be searched.
.IP "out_string" 12
pointer to null terminated return string, modified only if
return value is 0.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Search for a property in a device tree node and retrieve a null
terminated string value (pointer to data, not a copy). Returns 0 on
success, -EINVAL if the property does not exist, -ENODATA if property
does not have a value, and -EILSEQ if the string is not null-terminated
within the length of the property data.

The out_string pointer is modified only if a valid string can be decoded.
